dc_description_s: This data represents public land survey system (PLSS) corners for Sauk County, Wisconsin in 2020 and includes the layers 'Sauk_PLSSCorners_2020', 'Sauk_PLSSQuarterSection_2020', 'Sauk_PLSSSection_2020', and 'Sauk_PLSSTownship_2020'. [Corners: The current control point on the surface of the earth and its associated current coordinate value, generally determined by a surveying process and used to define an extremity of a boundary.QuarterSection: The second division of the PLSS and commonly called a quarter section.Section: The first division of the PLSS and commonly called a section.Township: In the Public Land Survey System a Township refers to a unit of land, that is nominally six miles on a side, usually containing 36 sections.]
